[YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

The primary responsibilities of this role, Production and Data Science Intern, are to:
Independently perform data analyses and apply statistics, computer programming, predictive modeling acumen to unsolved business goals;
Drive research laboratory optimization by creating predictive and/or optimization models that enhance the efficiency of labs’ capacity planning and quality detection;
Create and ensure adoption of predictive/machine learning models that drive Crop Science pipeline decisions;
Assist with development of new methods and process improvements;
Integrate solutions into production IT system by partnering with engineering teams and end users to ensure scalability and adoption;
Form partnerships with cross-functional teams in Bayer (Breeding, Product Supply, IT) to drive unified reporting and optimization of complex workflows that span functions and countries;
Present compelling, validated stories to all levels of organization, including peers, senior management and internal customers to drive both strategic and operational changes in business;
Provide technical contributions leveraging business acumen in a fast-paced team environment to accelerate our efforts on building an analytics-driven product pipeline.

WHO YOU ARE

Your success will be driven by your demonstration of our LIFE values. More specifically related to this position, Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:

Required Qualifications:

Currently pursuing a science, a statistical/mathematical or an engineering Bachelor’s degree, Master’s degree or Ph.D. degree;
Intermediate proficiency in complex data analyses, mathematical/statistical modeling and programming skills using R, Python or other statistical programming languages;
Ability to turn complex data into predictive and prescriptive insights;
Ability to influence people at varying levels of responsibility.
Your application
