[Credit Sesame is a fast growing FinTech company, a pioneer and the leader in personal credit management with a disruptive vision for personal finance through its recent acquisition and entry into digital banking. Headquartered in the Bay Area with presence across the US and Canada and growing globally, Credit Sesame is helping consumers' cash work for their credit and their credit work for their cash by applying advanced data science, AI and machine learning for better financial wellness. Our purpose is to be the “go to” brand for financial wellness.

Credit Sesame is looking for a hands-on, highly technical and mission-driven Director of Data Science & Analytics to lead and scale our fast growing Data Science, Machine Learning & Analytics team. Reporting to our Chief Technology Officer, you’ll lead a team transforming, analyzing, and interpreting data and leading experimentation across all levels of the company to drive key business decisions.
You'll...
scale, lead, and run a premier data science and analytics team that creates tangible impact through meaningful insights;
establish the goals, strategy, and priorities for your team and optimize team operational procedures;
use predictive modeling techniques to improve our product recommendation engine;
partner and collaborate with diverse teams in product, engineering, marketing, finance, and operations to help build and define roadmaps and strategies;
establish best practices for model life-cycle, EDA processes and quality management;
play a critical role in building the corporate insight repository and data-informed culture at Credit Sesame;
participate with Credit Sesame’s executive team, helping to set business strategy, discussing key strategic topics, and driving bold high-impact decisions.
You're a great fit for our team because...
you have grown and led a data science team, and have served as an expert to other data scientists, in a cross-functional organization where your team needs to collaborate with other teams across multiple business units;
you have experience with consumer facing products;
you have strong experience with statistical models, feature engineering, and algorithmic modeling;
you've built models for products and have a live model currently in production;
you’re experienced with SQL, Python, and related statistical analysis tools;
you’re hands-on and excited about dedicating a large percentage of your time to both building models and mentoring others who are doing so;
you have experience in model lifecycle management;
you have a strong business acumen, and are comfortable driving process change and continuous improvement.
You'll love it here because...
you‘ll have huge potential to grow with a company that’s a category leader;
you’ll have equity in a pre-IPO company backed by top VCs;
we offer comprehensive medical, dental, and vision insurance with many plan options;
we have lunch catered daily;
you can stay on top of your fitness goals with our onsite fitness centers;
we offer monthly fitness, phone and internet reimbursement;
you can fuel up at our stocked kitchens with endless snacks and drinks;
we prize EQ and empathy, and have a culture that emphasizes total wellness, including work-life harmony.


Office Location

We are open to hiring remotely for this role. You could also work out of our Toronto, San Francisco or our Mountain View office—you decide!

We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender, gender identity or expression, or veteran status. We are proud to be an equal opportunity workplace.]

[YOUR TASKS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

The primary responsibilities of this role, Head of Data Science and Analytics, are to:
Lead multiple teams of data scientists and data engineers providing mid- to long-term strategic, tactical direction and operational oversight to define, implement and promote cutting-edge analytical and data engineering solutions for complex Breeding problems and operations;
Serve as a thought leader for truly innovative ideas for long term impact on product development and placement;
Partner with other functions working on data science, software engineering, genome design, precision breeding, phenomics to ensure collaborative development of tools and techniques;
Contribute as a member of initiative teams working on multiple Global Breeding strategy areas;
Develop strong partnerships with other teams in Global Breeding and Biotechnology to ensure broad utility and impact of results;
Develop a broad knowledge of global internal and external advances and plans pertaining to new breeding methodologies and tools;
Identify and lead efforts around Breeding precision placement strategies and testing footprint;
Conduct research and be a key partner to advance the collective knowledge and skills of our Data Science practice across the enterprise.

WHO YOU ARE

Your success will be driven by your demonstration of our LIFE values. More specifically related to this position, Bayer seeks an incumbent who possesses the following:

Required Qualifications:

Ph.D. in Engineering, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics, Bioinformatics, Molecular Genetics, Genomics, Statistics or related field;
At least four years of experience leading data scientists at various levels of experience;
Strong knowledge of genetics, statistics, ML algorithms and frameworks, or frameworks such as CPLEX, IaaS and PaaS such as AWS, Google Cloud;
At least three years of experience of applying ML technologies to drive business outcomes;
Fluency in programming and scripting languages;
Strong problem solving and critical thinking skills;
Experience presenting results to varied audiences and influencing project direction/strategy;
Demonstrated ability to foster and maintain relationships at all levels of the organization and collaborating across various levels;
Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to work effectively in a team-based and cross-functional team environment.
